OL,3,GSouth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FCloudy at first, with mist
OL,6,Fpatches and the odd spot of drizzle
OL,7,Fnear western coasts. However, this
OL,8,Fwill clear and skies will brighten
OL,9,Fthrough the afternoon with warm sunny
OL,10,Fspells developing. Winds mostly light,
OL,11,Fthough breezier in the far west.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FA dry and clear start to the
OL,14,Fnight. However, low cloud will
OL,15,Fgradually move into Cornwall and west
OL,16,FDevon, and could bring some spots of
OL,17,Fdrizzle. Staying very mild.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
